-----------------
   thickedge
-----------------

Original purpose is to provide a simple routine for STL mesh edges
visualization.
STL does not support edges; it describes faces only. This routine
extract the edges from the mesh and creates tubes around each edge.

Usage:
 [shell]$ thickedge [-i/--input-file x] [-o/--output-file x] [-f/--faces x] [-r/--radius x] [-h/--help]
        -i/--input-file : STL input file name (Required).
        -o/--output-file : STL output file name (Required).
        -f/--faces : Number of faces of the tubes (default to 3) (Optional).
        -r/--radius : Radius of the tubes (default to 0.01) (Optional).
        -h/--help : Display a brief help (Optional).

Requirement: 
- VTK-7.x (www.vtk.org)

Uses yaap as a submodule (github.com/jeromevelut/yaap.git)
